WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:00.940
THEME SONG: Let's go!

00:00.940 --> 00:05.730
Peter Rabbit-- Go on a
run, run for our lives.

00:05.730 --> 00:08.500
We'll tear a hole in every
fence and every wall.

00:08.500 --> 00:13.380
Peter Rabbit-- Run through
the fields, run wild and free.

00:13.380 --> 00:17.160
And grab a piece of
every radish that we see!

00:17.160 --> 00:21.090
Go day and night, go for it all.

00:21.090 --> 00:24.040
It's time to fly, come on,
the winds begun to flow.

00:24.040 --> 00:28.460
Let's go! 'Cause you and I we
weren't made for going slow.

00:28.460 --> 00:30.210
Adventure calls the game is on.

00:30.210 --> 00:30.910
Come on!

00:30.910 --> 00:31.610
Let's go!

00:31.610 --> 00:32.380
Peter Rabbit!

00:32.380 --> 00:33.370
Let's go!

00:33.370 --> 00:34.350
Peter Rabbit!

00:34.350 --> 00:35.330
Let's go!

00:35.330 --> 00:36.100
Peter Rabbit!

00:36.100 --> 00:36.800
Whoa!

00:36.800 --> 00:37.780
Let's go!

00:41.420 --> 00:42.550
PETER RABBIT
(VOICEOVER): The Tale

00:42.550 --> 00:44.450
of Cottontail's New Friend.

00:44.450 --> 00:47.940
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:02.440 --> 01:03.520
No sign of him.

01:03.520 --> 01:07.090
If that shrew catches us,
he's going to be really angry.

01:07.090 --> 01:09.130
These dandelions
are for everyone.

01:09.130 --> 01:12.930
He's just got to learn to share.

01:12.930 --> 01:18.150
[SNIFF]

01:18.150 --> 01:19.940
Lily, get down!

01:19.940 --> 01:22.250
No, I'm not hiding anymore.

01:22.250 --> 01:24.010
It's silly.

01:24.010 --> 01:25.500
He'll here you.

01:25.500 --> 01:30.470
I don't care, I'm not scared
of a nasty little shrew.

01:30.470 --> 01:31.820
Neither am I.

01:31.820 --> 01:34.820
If you're not scared, then
why were you creeping around?

01:34.820 --> 01:36.470
It's more fun that way.

01:36.470 --> 01:37.520
Yeah!

01:37.520 --> 01:39.259
More fun.

01:39.259 --> 01:43.690
So we all agree,
none of us are scared.

01:43.690 --> 01:47.170
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:49.160 --> 01:52.640
[CHOMP]

01:55.620 --> 01:57.740
Hands of my dandelions.

01:57.740 --> 01:59.460
[SCREAMING]

01:59.460 --> 02:01.810
Come back here.

02:01.810 --> 02:03.340
Give me back my dandelions.

02:07.580 --> 02:08.530
Aw!

02:08.530 --> 02:10.590
This isn't over.

02:10.590 --> 02:13.410
[GRUNTS]

02:13.410 --> 02:15.290
[LAUGHING]

02:15.290 --> 02:16.900
That was close.

02:16.900 --> 02:20.510
Sounds like you've
been having fun.

02:20.510 --> 02:22.450
Do I want to know what
you've been up to?

02:25.680 --> 02:27.300
I didn't think so.

02:27.300 --> 02:29.850
I'm taking some vegetable
stew over to Mr. Barnes.

02:29.850 --> 02:32.010
Can you watch Cottontail
while I'm gone?

02:32.010 --> 02:33.090
OK.

02:33.090 --> 02:34.590
We'll have dinner
when I get back.

02:34.590 --> 02:36.190
So don't fill up on--

02:36.190 --> 02:38.760
oh, I don't know, dandelions?

02:38.760 --> 02:40.050
We won't.

02:40.050 --> 02:44.540
I mean, what dandelions?

02:44.540 --> 02:46.079
All right, then.

02:46.079 --> 02:47.480
Be sure you're in charge.

02:47.480 --> 02:48.579
Keep an eye on Cottontail.

02:48.579 --> 02:51.540
[DOOR OPENS]

02:51.540 --> 02:54.800
[LAUGHING]

02:55.500 --> 03:00.440
Peter, play with me.

03:00.440 --> 03:02.100
Not now, Cottontail.

03:02.100 --> 03:03.690
Please.

03:03.690 --> 03:04.950
Sorry, maybe later.

03:09.200 --> 03:15.680
[GRUNTS] I'll teach
them to eat my dandelions.

03:15.680 --> 03:18.090
[KNOCKS]

03:18.090 --> 03:19.650
Did you just hear something?

03:19.650 --> 03:21.270
Yeah, my tummy.

03:21.270 --> 03:23.460
It's hungry.

03:23.460 --> 03:25.990
You spoil your appetite.

03:25.990 --> 03:29.820
Although, I suppose
just one can't hurt.

03:29.820 --> 03:31.300
Hey!

03:31.300 --> 03:33.760
[LAUGHS]

03:33.760 --> 03:39.460
[KNOCKS] Oh, boy,
they're in trouble now.

03:39.460 --> 03:42.520
I can't wait to see their faces.

03:42.520 --> 03:44.980
I want my dandelions
back, and I want them now.

03:44.980 --> 03:46.380
You've taken too many.

03:46.380 --> 03:49.710
I already have exactly
1,073 dandelions left

03:49.710 --> 03:50.930
handed are the thing.

03:50.930 --> 03:53.720
[LAUGHS]

03:53.720 --> 03:57.050
Is Peter Rabbit home?

03:57.050 --> 03:57.910
Oh.

03:57.910 --> 04:00.230
Well, what are you looking at?

04:00.230 --> 04:01.690
Precious shrew.

04:01.690 --> 04:04.110
[MUSIC PLAYING]

04:04.110 --> 04:05.050
Hey, get off.

04:05.050 --> 04:05.750
What are you doing?

04:05.750 --> 04:06.920
Or maybe [INAUDIBLE] dandelions.

04:06.920 --> 04:08.330
Let me go!

04:08.330 --> 04:09.030
Dolly.

04:14.690 --> 04:16.519
I'm sure I heard something.

04:16.519 --> 04:19.899
[GIGGLES]

04:20.870 --> 04:22.089
Everything all right?

04:22.089 --> 04:24.310
It's fine [INAUDIBLE].

04:24.310 --> 04:25.010
OK.

04:25.010 --> 04:26.690
Well, call if you need anything.

04:26.690 --> 04:28.580
OK.

04:28.580 --> 04:30.950
[DOOR SHUTS]

04:30.950 --> 04:32.720
[GIGGLES]

04:32.720 --> 04:33.550
OK.

04:33.550 --> 04:37.070
That's it little
rabbit, fun's over.

04:37.070 --> 04:38.920
I'm not your dolly.

04:38.920 --> 04:41.130
Dolly!

04:41.130 --> 04:47.580
[GIGGLES]

04:47.580 --> 04:48.580
Help!

04:48.580 --> 04:54.310
[GIGGLES] Dolly is cute.

04:54.310 --> 04:57.490
[CHEERING]

04:57.490 --> 04:59.110
She's after me.

04:59.110 --> 05:00.320
Help!

05:00.320 --> 05:01.440
Huh?

05:01.440 --> 05:03.770
I definitely didn't
imagine that.

05:14.380 --> 05:17.450
So I'm guessing you
want me to stay in here.

05:17.450 --> 05:20.830
[GIGGLES]

05:22.760 --> 05:23.720
Ha!

05:23.720 --> 05:25.750
What's he doing here?

05:25.750 --> 05:27.530
Shrew, my dolly.

05:27.530 --> 05:29.500
Get me out of here.

05:29.500 --> 05:31.480
Yeah, get him out of here.

05:31.480 --> 05:32.950
Cottontail, I'm sorry.

05:32.950 --> 05:34.790
But you can't keep him.

05:34.790 --> 05:38.190
[SIGHS]

05:39.650 --> 05:40.870
You can keep the dandelions.

05:40.870 --> 05:42.370
I don't care.

05:42.370 --> 05:44.140
That's lucky.

05:44.140 --> 05:44.840
Oh!

05:44.840 --> 05:46.040
Excuse me!

05:46.040 --> 05:47.860
Because we ate them already.

05:47.860 --> 05:51.390
Just keep that crazy
bunny away from me.

05:51.390 --> 05:52.860
[GRUNTS]

05:52.860 --> 05:54.320
Bye bye, shrew.

05:57.730 --> 06:00.490
I hate to see
Cottontail so sad.

06:00.490 --> 06:03.210
What could we do
to cheer her up?

06:03.210 --> 06:05.300
I know just the thing.

06:05.300 --> 06:08.530
She wants a shrew doll,
let's give her one.

06:08.530 --> 06:09.230
No way!

06:09.230 --> 06:11.630
Am I dressing up?

06:11.630 --> 06:14.450
I didn't mean
you, we'll make one.

06:14.450 --> 06:15.680
We can use this.

06:15.680 --> 06:17.400
Great idea!

06:17.400 --> 06:20.390
And these will make
great eyes just in case

06:20.390 --> 06:21.920
forget just in case.

06:21.920 --> 06:25.280
[MUSIC PLAYING]

06:29.600 --> 06:32.000
Surprise!

06:32.000 --> 06:33.940
Huh?

06:33.940 --> 06:35.100
Where's Cottontail?

06:35.100 --> 06:38.270
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

06:40.690 --> 06:41.650
Oh, no!

06:47.200 --> 06:49.560
Oh, we should go back.

06:49.560 --> 06:51.350
It's not safe at night.

06:51.350 --> 06:55.050
We know it's not safe that's
why we have to find Cottontail.

06:55.050 --> 06:58.830
Luckily, we know where
she's heading, to the shrew.

06:58.830 --> 07:01.640
The shrew won't
be happy to see us.

07:01.640 --> 07:05.640
He's never happy
to see anyone.

07:05.640 --> 07:09.040
[LAUGHS]

07:16.350 --> 07:18.780
Benjamin!

07:18.780 --> 07:20.250
It's all brown.

07:20.250 --> 07:23.110
Run!

07:23.110 --> 07:23.820
Tail feathers.

07:28.420 --> 07:30.990
I think that grumpy
old owl has gone.

07:30.990 --> 07:31.770
No, wait.

07:31.770 --> 07:36.150
Maybe we should try to lead
to longer just to be sure.

07:36.150 --> 07:37.310
We can't wait!

07:37.310 --> 07:41.070
Cottontail is out here
too, and it's all my fault.

07:41.070 --> 07:43.520
If I just played with her
like she asked, none of these

07:43.520 --> 07:44.480
would have happened.

07:51.190 --> 07:53.659
That will stopped those
rabbits from coming back.

07:53.659 --> 07:55.310
Excuse me.

07:55.310 --> 07:57.260
Have you seen Cottontail?

07:57.260 --> 07:59.300
No, I haven't seen
that crazy little rabbit.

07:59.300 --> 08:00.660
Don't tell me she is loose?

08:00.660 --> 08:03.620
Oh, she'll make me wear a dress.

08:03.620 --> 08:05.840
I was sure she'd be here.

08:05.840 --> 08:08.790
Oh, she must be lost.

08:08.790 --> 08:11.140
Shrew?

08:11.140 --> 08:11.840
Shrew?

08:14.740 --> 08:15.440
Shrew!

08:19.910 --> 08:22.390
Owl bird's heading this way.

08:22.390 --> 08:24.400
Then shouldn't we
be heading that way.

08:24.400 --> 08:29.200
It looks like he's circling,
he must be hunting something.

08:29.200 --> 08:30.190
Cottontail!

08:34.140 --> 08:37.110
Follow that [INAUDIBLE].

08:37.110 --> 08:38.100
Shrew?

08:38.100 --> 08:39.280
Shrew?

08:39.280 --> 08:39.980
Shrew?

08:41.940 --> 08:43.890
Birdie.

08:43.890 --> 08:47.810
Hello birdie.

08:47.810 --> 08:49.270
Tail feathers.

08:49.270 --> 08:54.090
The tasty morsel missed,
but not for long.

08:54.090 --> 08:55.390
Pica!

08:55.390 --> 08:57.710
Don't worry Cottontail,
you're safe now.

08:57.710 --> 08:59.390
We can't stay here all night.

08:59.390 --> 09:01.970
Owls don't stop hunting till
they've caught something.

09:01.970 --> 09:05.010
I know that for a fact.

09:05.010 --> 09:08.170
Never to breathe,
never to breathe.

09:08.170 --> 09:09.660
Dolly!

09:09.660 --> 09:13.130
[GIGGLES]

09:13.130 --> 09:16.140
Cottontail.

09:16.140 --> 09:16.920
Wait!

09:16.920 --> 09:18.280
I've got a plan.

09:18.280 --> 09:21.470
It's risky, but it
might just work.

09:21.470 --> 09:22.940
Let's hope to it.

09:22.940 --> 09:28.020
You can't hide forever
you fluffy fools.

09:28.020 --> 09:31.340
There you are.

09:31.340 --> 09:34.190
Carrying a juicy baby bunny.

09:38.010 --> 09:39.890
You'll never get Cottontail.

09:43.800 --> 09:44.500
[MUSIC PLAYING]

09:44.500 --> 09:48.470
(SINGING) Run rabbit run, run
liked you've never run before.

09:51.940 --> 09:54.850
Run rabbit run, if he
catches you, you're done,

09:54.850 --> 09:55.840
so run some more.

09:58.990 --> 10:00.880
Your heart is pounding.

10:00.880 --> 10:02.690
Those seeds are sounding.

10:02.690 --> 10:05.650
So close to you,
what can you do?

10:05.650 --> 10:06.350
Oh!

10:06.350 --> 10:07.830
Run and run.

10:07.830 --> 10:10.300
You better run.

10:10.300 --> 10:12.780
I think I hear them
catching to you.

10:15.750 --> 10:26.170
[LAUGHS]

10:26.170 --> 10:28.150
Not that I care about
the little rabbits,

10:28.150 --> 10:30.950
but don't you think you
should go and rescue her?

10:30.950 --> 10:31.840
No need.

10:31.840 --> 10:34.520
Old Brown hasn't
got her, we have.

10:34.520 --> 10:35.220
Shrew!

10:37.990 --> 10:39.990
Birdie gone.

10:39.990 --> 10:41.040
Long gone.

10:41.040 --> 10:44.140
[LAUGHING]

10:44.840 --> 10:46.370
Let's go home.

10:46.370 --> 10:47.810
I have a feeling
Old Brown would be

10:47.810 --> 10:49.340
very happy when he gets home.

10:55.590 --> 10:57.750
I'm sorry about
today, Cottontail.

10:57.750 --> 10:59.970
I should have played
with you like you wanted.

10:59.970 --> 11:01.080
I'm not left you alone.

11:01.080 --> 11:04.580
[GIGGLES] Birdie funny.

11:04.580 --> 11:06.390
No, Cottontail.

11:06.390 --> 11:08.490
Birdie is not funny.

11:08.490 --> 11:11.260
So let's stay away from
Old Brown for a while.

11:14.090 --> 11:21.090
Rabbit stew, rabbit on
toast, or scrambled rabbit.

11:21.090 --> 11:22.610
No!

11:22.610 --> 11:24.880
[GRUNTS] Tail feathers!

11:28.540 --> 11:31.620
I'd like to see them sneak
up on my dandelions now.

11:34.620 --> 11:36.120
[GIGGLES] Shrew!

11:40.620 --> 11:41.520
THEME SONG: Peter Rabbit!

11:44.520 --> 11:45.420
Peter Rabbit!

11:52.020 --> 11:53.820
Peter Rabbit!

11:53.820 --> 11:55.920
Peter Rabbit!

11:55.920 --> 11:58.070
Peter Rabbit!
